<h3>Placing an Observation Marker</h3>
<p style="text-align: left;">Your observation latitude and longitude is automatically recorded by placing an observation marker <img src="http://cit3.ldl.swin.edu.au/~vital/bws/images/person.png" /><br /> on the map.</p>
<p style="text-align: left;">To place a marker simply click anywhere on the map. The marker can then be dragged to the location of the observation.</p>
<p style="text-align: left;">You can use the zoom tool to help locate your observation point.</p> 
<p style="text-align: left;">Please note that you can place more than one marker but only the final position of the last marker is recorded.</p>
